I am here to explore my interests, to share my experiences, and to promote resiliency in this space. Every environment has its challenges, for which we need to be prepared - physically, mentally, emotionally, spiritually. We are all leaders in this space. We all make an impact.

I have learned that my success cannot be defined by anyone else's experiences or expectations because when I compare myself to others or work to please others, I am not being true to myself. The best way I can help myself, and others, is to be my authentic self & speak my truth.
Those times when I felt defeated and walked away from something, often - unexpectedly - I was led to something more fulfilling. I believe this happened because I aligned my actions with my values.

I have been "making it" for 45 years in this world, in many different environments. I have not always been successful by my own definition at the time, but I have been continuously learning & developing. I have even "given up" a few times, when my situation seemed unfit for me.üßµ
Take a moment to really appreciate how far you have come. Keep dreaming. Keep doing. üí´

I speak from experience. I have failed forward. I encourage exploration. I love unconditionally‚Ä¶ and fiercely. I do have some stories. Much of my experience is founded in failure, which represents a different level of success. I am a seeker of truth and harmony in life and love.

I wanted to prove to the world that women are more than a pretty face - we are smart, and capable, and sexual, and sensual. I may not have proven that notion to the world or to my parents, but my experiences allowed me to connect with my kids on an entirely different level. (4/?)

I was smart, but I was sassy. I reached for the stars. I swung for the fences. I was experimental. I wanted to explore every notion and understand everything on a deeper level than did my parents. I was perpetually evolving to the circumstances of a rapidly changing world. (3/?)

But I rebelled. I was a free spirit, not to be contained. I was curious. I wanted to know about the world and my existence, my feelings, my thoughts, my desires. I wanted to understand if others felt the same. I wanted to explore life and love. I have never played it safe (2/?)

üë£ TruthBeTold, my past is full of lessons, most of which I learned the hard way. I am grateful for the insights I gained by challenging perspectives, breaking boundaries, and forging my own path, however painful it was at any given moment. My parents tried to protect me‚Ä¶(1/?)
